  "texts": [
    "The simple noise model is described as follows:",
    "Here, f n is a T × 1 time-series vector of firing rates for channel n where T represents the number of 20-ms time bins, Σ is the T × T diagonal covariance matrix, and σ is the standard deviation.",
    "This was a simple noise model with a diagonal covariance matrix used for all channels (i.e., the same σ was used for all channels).",
    "We understand that more sophisticated noise models could have been used, but our simplified approach was well enough suited for single-bin decoding where one can assume independence between time bins which is further explained in Supplementary Fig. 4.",
    "After matching the fSNRs, we scaled the laterality coefficient vector where a value of 0 removed the laterality dimension completely, and a value of 1 matched the laterality coefficient magnitude of the real data."
  ],
